          <h1>Designing Zazzle.com Settings</h1>
          <p class="subtitle">A look into the design process.</p>

          <p class="lead">As my second project since joining the Zazzle team as a Product Manager Intern in January, I took on the task of redesigning the settings pages on Zazzle.com.</p>

          <p>This project was started near the end of March of 2015. While there were a number of other exciting projects ongoing, I wanted to take on a project that I could work through from the beginning all the way to the very end - from ideation all the way to implementation. Coupled with the fact that my internship was coming to an end at the end of April 2015, this was the perfect project for me.</p>

          <p>While not entirely public facing, the settings pages play an instrumental role on Zazzle.com. Any changes that need to be made to a user's profile and account, or to a store owner's products and payment information are entered on these pages.</p>

          <p><strong>Like with the {{#link-to 'post.design-analysis-zazzle-maker'}}Zazzle Maker Dashboard{{/link-to}}, I took on the duo role of both a product designer and product manager.</strong> I was the primary designer and was responsible for the creation of all designs, mockups, and wireframes. I also worked together with another PM to define specifications and manage development for the implementation of the settings pages.</p>
